obo:ECO_0000314  a  owl:Class .

obo:GO_0098978  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_4556  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: With respect to subcellular localization, immunohistochemical, biochemical, and electron microscopy analysis in rat brain clearly delineated that Sipa1l3/SPAR3 protein is present within the postsynaptic compartment (Fig. 3 and p. 34).\n\nSipa1l3/SPAR3 is found in synapses characterized by the presence of PSD95, VGLUT1 (Fig. 3b) and Bassoon (Fig. 4b) and is absent from synapses carrying GABAA receptors and VGAT (Fig. 3b).\n\nSipa1l3/SPAR3 bind to ProSAPiP1/Lzts3 - a component of the postsynaptic Shank scaffolding platform (Fig. 4d,e).. Experimental description: \"Rats from both sexes (Sprague-Dawley) were purchased from Charles River, Germany.\" (Materials and Methods/Animals and ethics statement, p. 29).\n\n\"Primary antibodies\nAn anti-Sipa1l3/SPAR3 antibody directed against the C-terminus of the protein (aa 1300-1776) was generated in rabbit after injection of a GST-SPAR3C-term fusion protein (anti-SPAR3, Pineda, Germany)\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" ;
        dc:date           "2022-04-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4556" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

